(Entrance, Odd Number)

25
00:03:21,865 --> 00:03:22,585
Why are you here?

26
00:03:22,946 --> 00:03:23,826
Why are you here?

27
00:03:28,946 --> 00:03:29,865
Xu Jingjing.

28
00:03:31,625 --> 00:03:32,625
Kang Jiawei!

29
00:03:37,025 --> 00:03:37,786
Screw you.

30
00:03:38,025 --> 00:03:38,425
I...

31
00:03:56,585 --> 00:03:57,386
Xu Jingjing.

32
00:04:00,786 --> 00:04:02,025
Your family is not here?

33
00:04:06,826 --> 00:04:07,546
It's fine.

34
00:04:07,946 --> 00:04:08,745
I don't mind.

35
00:04:10,425 --> 00:04:11,386
It shouldn't be like this.

36
00:04:15,745 --> 00:04:16,745
Here's a present for you.

37
00:04:22,305 --> 00:04:23,026
What is this?

38
00:04:23,466 --> 00:04:24,305
Is this a coming-of-age gift?

39
00:04:25,425 --> 00:04:26,305
Don't get too touched.

40
00:04:27,146 --> 00:04:28,786
It was nothing expensive.

41
00:04:31,865 --> 00:04:32,586
What is it?

42
00:04:33,346 --> 00:04:34,185
They told me

43
00:04:35,425 --> 00:04:36,825
it's a special weapon

44
00:04:37,265 --> 00:04:38,265
for art students.

45
00:04:39,945 --> 00:04:40,706
Special weapon?

46
00:04:41,346 --> 00:04:42,226
A pencil sharpener.

47
00:04:44,666 --> 00:04:45,945
A pencil sharpener?

48
00:04:46,226 --> 00:04:47,986
How much is it worth?

49
00:04:48,385 --> 00:04:49,425
If you think it's cheap, then...

50
00:04:49,945 --> 00:04:50,825
No. I've never said that.

51
00:04:51,146 --> 00:04:51,706
Don't worry.

52
00:04:52,065 --> 00:04:52,786
I like it a lot.

53
00:04:53,625 --> 00:04:55,586
I'll use it every day.

54
00:04:55,945 --> 00:04:57,505
Sharpen your pencils and draw more.

55
00:04:57,706 --> 00:04:58,265
Then, you'll forget

56
00:04:58,425 --> 00:04:59,425
all your troubles.

57
00:05:03,065 --> 00:05:03,786
Xu Jingjing.

58
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,265
I have a present for you too.

59
00:05:08,346 --> 00:05:09,346
It's a novel written

60
00:05:10,185 --> 00:05:12,065
by my favorite author, Lawrence Block.

61
00:05:12,466 --> 00:05:13,346
I got you the whole set.

62
00:05:13,786 --> 00:05:15,226
Happy coming-of-age day.

63
00:05:16,385 --> 00:05:17,226
Thank you.

64
00:05:21,185 --> 00:05:22,065
Read more.

65
00:05:22,385 --> 00:05:23,185
It can help

66
00:05:23,346 --> 00:05:24,106
with your creative thinking.

67
00:05:24,706 --> 00:05:25,945
It's good for art students.

68
00:05:26,706 --> 00:05:27,865
This one.

69
00:05:28,026 --> 00:05:28,945
8 Million Ways to Die.

70
00:05:29,466 --> 00:05:31,786
They will always leave behind some...

71
00:05:31,786 --> 00:05:33,226
Sure. Thank you.

72
00:05:33,385 --> 00:05:34,906
Let me bring them
to the classroom first.

73
00:05:35,185 --> 00:05:35,786
Let me help you.

74
00:05:37,346 --> 00:05:37,945
Let me do it.

75
00:05:38,226 --> 00:05:39,106
I can do it. It's not that heavy.

76
00:05:39,546 --> 00:05:40,986
You shouldn't visit
someone else's classroom.

77
00:05:41,106 --> 00:05:41,945
It's fine. Give it to me.

78
00:05:41,986 --> 00:05:42,786
Enough, the two of you!

79
00:05:43,865 --> 00:05:44,745
I can do it myself.

80
00:05:45,305 --> 00:05:46,026
Give it to me.

81
00:05:57,106 --> 00:05:57,625
Stop right there.

82
00:06:00,466 --> 00:06:01,625
Kang Jiawei, I have a question for you.

83
00:06:02,786 --> 00:06:04,546
We made a promise.

84
00:06:04,786 --> 00:06:05,706
You would be my teacher

85
00:06:06,026 --> 00:06:06,666
and teach me

86
00:06:06,706 --> 00:06:07,825
how to make friends with Xu Jingjing.

87
00:06:08,026 --> 00:06:08,745
I trusted you.

88
00:06:08,906 --> 00:06:09,986
Yes. I can't fake it anymore.

89
00:06:11,305 --> 00:06:12,466
I don't want to be your teacher anymore.

90
00:06:13,906 --> 00:06:15,106
Then, let's call it off.

91
00:06:17,385 --> 00:06:18,146
Do you think

92
00:06:18,986 --> 00:06:21,106
she prefers the pencil sharpener

93
00:06:22,106 --> 00:06:23,666
or detective novels?

94
00:06:26,346 --> 00:06:26,906
Yes.

95
00:06:27,906 --> 00:06:28,945
The pencil sharpener
might be very useful

96
00:06:29,065 --> 00:06:29,786
for her.

97
00:06:30,546 --> 00:06:31,706
But if she reads

98
00:06:32,106 --> 00:06:33,106
the novels I got for her,

99
00:06:33,505 --> 00:06:34,786
it'll influence her positively.

100
00:06:35,305 --> 00:06:36,226
Besides,

101
00:06:36,385 --> 00:06:37,385
it's wrong

102
00:06:37,546 --> 00:06:38,226
to call it a detective novel.

103
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:39,865
Lawrence Block writes

104
00:06:40,026 --> 00:06:41,026
crime fictions.

105
00:06:42,146 --> 00:06:43,505
It was just a metaphor.

106
00:06:43,666 --> 00:06:45,065
Do you know what's a metaphor?

107
00:06:50,546 --> 00:06:51,185
The police academy you're applying to

108
00:06:51,265 --> 00:06:52,065
is in Beijing, right?

109
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:53,305
Yes.

110
00:06:53,745 --> 00:06:54,385
What about you?

111
00:06:54,706 --> 00:06:55,625
I'm planning
to apply for Fuxing University.

112
00:06:56,226 --> 00:06:57,226
I want to stay here.

113
00:06:58,906 --> 00:07:00,385
As far as I know,

114
00:07:00,865 --> 00:07:02,265
the best designing courses

115
00:07:02,865 --> 00:07:04,346
and the best art courses

116
00:07:04,706 --> 00:07:05,986
are in Beijing.

117
00:07:06,265 --> 00:07:07,825
As far as I know,

118
00:07:08,865 --> 00:07:10,026
the designing course
in Fuxing University

119
00:07:10,305 --> 00:07:12,265
is the best in the country.

120
00:07:13,226 --> 00:07:14,305
I think it's better in Beijing.

121
00:07:14,505 --> 00:07:15,385
I think Wuxi is better.

122
00:07:15,385 --> 00:07:16,706
You get roasted duck in Beijing.

123
00:07:16,786 --> 00:07:17,945
You get
sweet and sour pork ribs in Wuxi.

124
00:07:18,106 --> 00:07:18,986
That's Xu Jingjing's favorite.

125
00:07:19,226 --> 00:07:20,226
The Great Wall is in Beijing.

126
00:07:20,385 --> 00:07:21,106
Lake Tai is in Wuxi.

127
00:07:21,226 --> 00:07:21,945
It's full of fish.

128
00:07:22,065 --> 00:07:23,106
There'll never be a shortage of food.

129
00:07:29,786 --> 00:07:31,865
There's still some time

130
00:07:32,026 --> 00:07:32,945
before we start college.

131
00:07:33,825 --> 00:07:34,586
Let's leave it

132
00:07:34,625 --> 00:07:35,546
for Jingjing to decide.

133
00:07:36,586 --> 00:07:37,346
I agree.

134
00:07:46,425 --> 00:07:46,865
Jingjing.

135
00:07:47,385 --> 00:07:47,945
Jingjing.

136
00:07:48,906 --> 00:07:49,625
Sorry.

137
00:07:49,865 --> 00:07:50,466
Can we still make it?

138
00:07:50,706 --> 00:07:51,305
Hurry up.

139
00:07:51,425 --> 00:07:51,906
It's over.

140
00:07:52,065 --> 00:07:52,906
Why are you here?

141
00:07:53,065 --> 00:07:53,706
It's over?

142
00:07:55,586 --> 00:07:56,546
But... I...

143
00:07:59,745 --> 00:08:00,625
Happy coming-of-age day.

144
00:08:05,745 --> 00:08:07,385
The present... I...

145
00:08:07,706 --> 00:08:08,625
If you don't want to come here,
you don't have to.

146
00:08:08,945 --> 00:08:09,706
I don't mind.

147
00:08:09,945 --> 00:08:10,346
No.

148
00:08:10,706 --> 00:08:11,106
Jingjing.

149
00:08:11,505 --> 00:08:12,586
Of course, I want to be here.

150
00:08:13,106 --> 00:08:14,666
I got into a rear-end collision
just now.

151
00:08:14,865 --> 00:08:15,906
The driver refused to let me go.

152
00:08:16,065 --> 00:08:17,265
He insisted on waiting
for the police's arrival.

153
00:08:17,385 --> 00:08:18,586
How did the collision happen?

154
00:08:18,945 --> 00:08:19,425
Did you attend

155
00:08:19,425 --> 00:08:20,425
another wedding?

156
00:08:20,745 --> 00:08:21,305
Are the couple

157
00:08:21,385 --> 00:08:22,505
more important than me?

158
00:08:22,745 --> 00:08:23,945
All my friends' parents were there,

159
00:08:24,146 --> 00:08:24,986
except for mine.

160
00:08:25,226 --> 00:08:26,226
I come home dog-tired every day

161
00:08:26,385 --> 00:08:27,346
after work.

162
00:08:27,706 --> 00:08:28,986
And you welcome me with a long face.

163
00:08:29,226 --> 00:08:30,305
It's my fault, all right?

164
00:08:30,786 --> 00:08:31,466
Jingjing, listen.

165
00:08:31,546 --> 00:08:32,706
Of course, you're more important
than them.

166
00:08:32,865 --> 00:08:33,466
No.

167
00:08:33,785 --> 00:08:34,306
I don't need

168
00:08:34,466 --> 00:08:35,625
your wishes.

169
00:08:37,025 --> 00:08:37,665
Jingjing.

170
00:08:38,346 --> 00:08:39,226
Jingjing.

171
00:08:55,905 --> 00:08:56,545
Mr. Xu.

172
00:08:58,745 --> 00:08:59,265
Mr. Kang.

173
00:08:59,745 --> 00:09:00,865
Why weren't you there just now?

174
00:09:01,745 --> 00:09:02,466
Don't bring it up.

175
00:09:03,346 --> 00:09:03,986
I was supposed

176
00:09:03,986 --> 00:09:05,625
to host a wedding today.

177
00:09:05,826 --> 00:09:06,865
I thought

178
00:09:07,066 --> 00:09:07,665
I would have ample time to come here

179
00:09:07,826 --> 00:09:09,385
after the event.

180
00:09:09,586 --> 00:09:10,665
I didn't expect

181
00:09:10,785 --> 00:09:11,785
to get caught up in the traffic.

182
00:09:11,905 --> 00:09:13,385
I was nervous and tried to rush here,

183
00:09:14,346 --> 00:09:15,625
so I ended up in a rear-end collision.

184
00:09:16,426 --> 00:09:17,346
I had to wait

185
00:09:17,545 --> 00:09:18,265
for the police to settle the conflict

186
00:09:18,306 --> 00:09:19,226
before I could come here.

187
00:09:20,066 --> 00:09:21,066
And the Coming-of-age Ceremony was over.

188
00:09:21,265 --> 00:09:22,306
Did Xu Jingjing know

189
00:09:22,785 --> 00:09:24,106
about the paint you got for her?

190
00:09:25,385 --> 00:09:26,226
How did you know about that?

191
00:09:27,145 --> 00:09:28,145
I saw you

192
00:09:28,346 --> 00:09:29,226
at the store yesterday.

193
00:09:31,586 --> 00:09:32,106
It won't be helpful anyway.

194
00:09:33,106 --> 00:09:34,466
For her,

195
00:09:34,665 --> 00:09:36,186
everything I do and I say now

196
00:09:36,545 --> 00:09:37,466
is wrong.

197
00:09:40,946 --> 00:09:41,466
All right, Mr. Kang.

198
00:09:42,226 --> 00:09:43,145
I won't disturb you further.

199
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:44,426
I'll get going.

200
00:10:00,586 --> 00:10:01,545
Remember to get the basketball later,

201
00:10:01,745 --> 00:10:02,466
Dapeng.

202
00:10:03,586 --> 00:10:04,306
I'll get going.

203
00:10:04,946 --> 00:10:05,665
What's the matter, Jiayao?

204
00:10:06,505 --> 00:10:07,186
This one is for you.

205
00:10:10,986 --> 00:10:11,665
For me?

206
00:10:13,466 --> 00:10:15,226
Happy coming-of-age day!

207
00:10:26,106 --> 00:10:26,826
That's great!

208
00:10:26,905 --> 00:10:28,346
I got a gift from Wang Jiayao!

209
00:10:29,226 --> 00:10:30,625
Jingjing's mom looks so pretty.

210
00:10:30,826 --> 00:10:31,385
You look

211
00:10:31,505 --> 00:10:32,785
like Jingjing's sister.

212
00:10:32,986 --> 00:10:33,625
I'm flattered.

213
00:10:33,865 --> 00:10:35,466
No way I'm her sister.

214
00:10:36,545 --> 00:10:37,986
When is Jingjing going

215
00:10:38,186 --> 00:10:39,306
to take the entrance exam
for the dance academy?

216
00:10:39,586 --> 00:10:40,745
Soon. She'll take it
during the winter break.

217
00:10:42,186 --> 00:10:43,586
Jingjing can definitely do it.

218
00:10:43,745 --> 00:10:44,785
Of course.

219
00:10:45,426 --> 00:10:46,226
Jingjing

220
00:10:46,385 --> 00:10:47,186
has been preparing for it

221
00:10:47,385 --> 00:10:48,505
since the beginning
of the summer vacation.

222
00:10:48,706 --> 00:10:49,545
That's so impressive.

223
00:10:49,905 --> 00:10:51,106
You should learn from her.

224
00:10:52,706 --> 00:10:53,306
Mom.

225
00:10:53,346 --> 00:10:54,905
Can I speak to my classmate?

226
00:10:55,706 --> 00:10:56,346
Go ahead.

227
00:10:59,186 --> 00:10:59,865
Wei Xue.

228
00:11:02,066 --> 00:11:03,226
Xu Jingjing.

229
00:11:13,986 --> 00:11:14,905
Is this for me?

230
00:11:15,706 --> 00:11:16,785
Happy Coming-to-age Day.

231
00:11:18,665 --> 00:11:19,466
Jingjing.

232
00:11:23,145 --> 00:11:24,186
It's a pair.

233
00:11:28,226 --> 00:11:29,466
I've accepted your apology.

234
00:11:30,066 --> 00:11:32,665
I need to apologize to you as well.

235
00:11:33,545 --> 00:11:34,346
I wasn't

236
00:11:34,625 --> 00:11:36,426
a good friend.

237
00:11:37,106 --> 00:11:38,106
I never listened

238
00:11:38,306 --> 00:11:39,186
to your thoughts.

239
00:11:40,625 --> 00:11:41,706
Let what happened when we were 17th

240
00:11:42,106 --> 00:11:43,625
stay in that year.

241
00:11:44,265 --> 00:11:45,145
From now on,

242
00:11:46,745 --> 00:11:48,306
let us start all over again, all right?

243
00:11:49,986 --> 00:11:51,706
Will you still

244
00:11:51,785 --> 00:11:53,025
be my friend?

245
00:11:55,145 --> 00:11:57,586
We weren't honest with each other.

246
00:11:58,106 --> 00:11:59,145
You were wary of me,

247
00:12:01,025 --> 00:12:02,226
and I doubted you.

248
00:12:02,826 --> 00:12:03,505
Friends

249
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:04,905
shouldn't be like that.

250
00:12:05,745 --> 00:12:06,545
From now on,

251
00:12:06,865 --> 00:12:07,665
we shall try

252
00:12:07,665 --> 00:12:08,346
telling each other our minds.

253
00:12:09,066 --> 00:12:09,745
What do you think?

254
00:12:11,865 --> 00:12:13,226
Let's get to know each other
all over again.

255
00:12:14,186 --> 00:12:15,665
My name is Wei Xue.

256
00:12:18,066 --> 00:12:19,106
My name is Xu Jingjing.

257
00:12:38,665 --> 00:12:40,106
(Strive hard, study hard.)
Thank you so much,

258
00:12:40,306 --> 00:12:40,905
Gao Zhan.

259
00:12:41,186 --> 00:12:41,946
Xu Jingjing.

260
00:12:43,706 --> 00:12:44,826
You misunderstood your dad.

261
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:47,106
What are you talking about?

262
00:12:47,466 --> 00:12:48,826
Mr. Xu didn't miss the ceremony
deliberately.

263
00:12:49,665 --> 00:12:50,946
He was caught in a rear-end collision.

264
00:12:52,706 --> 00:12:53,426
How did you know about that?

265
00:12:53,946 --> 00:12:54,905
Do you believe everything he says?

266
00:12:55,346 --> 00:12:56,986
I'm just not his priority.

267
00:12:57,466 --> 00:12:58,505
He didn't mean for that to happen.

268
00:13:02,346 --> 00:13:03,745
I didn't intend to tell you this

269
00:13:04,826 --> 00:13:06,066
because I hate spoilers the most.

270
00:13:08,066 --> 00:13:08,665
However,

271
00:13:08,665 --> 00:13:09,625
you really misunderstood Mr. Xu
this time.

272
00:13:11,826 --> 00:13:12,265
Tell her

273
00:13:12,426 --> 00:13:13,265
you bought the paint for her.

274
00:13:13,785 --> 00:13:14,625
She won't want it

275
00:13:14,745 --> 00:13:15,505
if she knows it's from me.

276
00:13:17,586 --> 00:13:18,346
Why don't we repaint the wall

277
00:13:19,505 --> 00:13:20,586
if she doesn't want it?

278
00:13:21,426 --> 00:13:22,186
It's not the right time

279
00:13:22,265 --> 00:13:23,265
to joke.

280
00:13:27,346 --> 00:13:28,625
I'm so useless.

281
00:13:30,665 --> 00:13:31,665
You didn't do it on purpose.

282
00:13:32,226 --> 00:13:32,745
It's fine.

283
00:13:32,946 --> 00:13:33,826
I'll talk to her

284
00:13:34,106 --> 00:13:34,745
when she comes home later.

